website_summaries.verdict: Packed with premium meats and protein, this is a simple yet delicious duck pate made without wheat, chicken by-products, or grains for a nutritious limited ingredient diet.
pros: Duck, turkey broth, and chicken liver are the first 3 ingredients
Loaded with vitamins, minerals, and omega-3 fatty acids for healthy skin and coat
cons: While cats of all ages enjoy this meaty meal, Blue Buffalo Wilderness is one of the more expensive canned foods

customer_reviews.title: Quality control isn't up to par
customer_reviews.text: The manufacturer needs better quality control. Of the 24 cans purchased 3 were dented. One can was dented so badly the top popped open spilling cat food on the inside of the shrink wrap. The shrink wrap showed no puncture or abnormal stretching to indicate exterior damage. In addition, the box that the cans were shipped in was in pristine condition. I spend too much money on this cat food to have waste from poor canning.
customer_reviews.author: Nea

customer_reviews.title: Do not purchase this product here
customer_reviews.text: Should have listened to the reviews. The food was not the same that I usually purchase at petco. There were large pieces of bone in the food and it smelled bad. Neither of my cats would touch it. They love the same food when I buy at the store.
customer_reviews.author: kelly

customer_reviews.title: Your husband will never taste the difference!
customer_reviews.text: i secretly add this to my husband's post-workout shakes because i hate him. so far he hasn't noticed.
customer_reviews.author: Mollz

customer_reviews.title: Inconsistent formula
customer_reviews.text: My cats loved this turkey flavor, and I was so happy to get them on a healthier diet. That was the first batch. I ordered the second batch, but from the first can, my cats won't touch it. Now I'm stuck with a case of cat food. What changed from one batch to another? I definitely won't buy again when the formula is so inconsistent from one batch to another. I'm going to try to return it.
customer_reviews.author: Rose M. J.

customer_reviews.title: Cat Will Not Eat It
customer_reviews.text: So disappointed in this one. The salmon flavor has lots of bones in it which I didn't mind but it does not smell good and my cat will just eat a little bit and then try to cover it up. He was a stray and he has never been picky about any food, but he seems to hate this wet food. Really disappointed to have spent so much on it and not be able to use it. Will continue to look elsewhere for a quality wet food.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: This is not wilderness.
customer_reviews.text: There is something wrong with this food. I chose to ignore the reviews saying that the food was bad, and I should have just listened. There is definitely something wrong with this batch of cans. Usually its pink tinged, and more solid. This is grey mush floating in gravy. My boy wont even acknowledge it, just tries to bury it and walks away. I'm done with pet food on here, I'm not sure why but the quality is not the same. And the fact they they dont do returns on pet food is really hurting my wallet.
customer_reviews.author: The Viking Ninja

customer_reviews.title: Salmon Soup, Cat Hates It
customer_reviews.text: I am kicking myself that I ordered this online. Big difference from the in store version. Can is much larger. The salmon arrives as a nasty soup. Nothing holds it together, it has no firmness. My cat liked the smaller store brand but won't even touch the Salmon Soup. I flushed 40 bucks down the drain buying this online - the cat food is soon to follow. Buyer beware.
customer_reviews.author: Michael Patrick

customer_reviews.title: Buy at your own risk
customer_reviews.text: Buy at your own risk this food is making my cat sick. I opened up a can today to find mold .this is very unacceptable .
customer_reviews.author: jenn

customer_reviews.title: 2 bad batches
customer_reviews.text: My cat loved the first case of this I bought, but the second case came and she refused to touch it. Amazon was kind enough to replace it, the next case was fine and she was super happy. Fast forward a bit, third case comes and again, she won't touch it. There has to be something wrong with it that I can't smell or see. I won't keep buying this food if 50% of the time there's something wrong with it. I worry about giving my cat something that might make her sick. I will stick to the dry food now.
customer_reviews.author: Jennifer

customer_reviews.title: The cans of food were bad, It's way too expensive to have this happen
customer_reviews.text: Hello: I do always hate to write a bad review, but I buy this for my daughter for her cats. At the time, she was out of food, and when she opened several cans of the meat were bad, she had to throw those away, and i feel that the price is a bit high, but if you choose to purchase it, should be good. It put her in a bad place as she went thru several cans before she found a good one but now wonders about future orders. I know these things happen, but it shouldn't
customer_reviews.author: ajb5456

customer_reviews.title: My old housecat LOVES this stuff!
customer_reviews.text: He tells me how much too! No, I'm not the crazy cat lady he just meows at feeding time to let me know that he is ready to eat. He's rather old, and last year we noticed that he was losing a lot of weight. What a difference a year makes! He just celebrated his 72nd birthday (in human years), and he acts like a kitten again. He's running around the house, jumping up and down, and I don't see any gray hair yet. Thank you Blue Buffalo for giving me a few more precious years with my baby boy.
customer_reviews.author: SquarePeg

customer_reviews.title: What's up with the 3oz tins of salmon??
customer_reviews.text: I've been buying Blue Buffalo canned cat food for years. My cats have always loved the salmon flavor, so for my fast purchased I decided to get only salmon (3oz cans) versus the variety pack I usually get. When I opened the first can, I noticed it had a VERY pungent smell which I can only described as putrid. I thought it was just me, but the cats would not go near it. I opened a second can... same thing. As an experiment, I purchased 2 5oz cans from the local PetSmart and they were OK. There goes $20 down the garbage disposal.
customer_reviews.author: jg

customer_reviews.title: Most of my cats don't love this.
customer_reviews.text: I am comfortable enough with Blue Buffalo quality, as far as I know, but my cats don't prefer this food. The youngest cats (still not fully adults) are easier to please since they're always hungry it seems, so they will eat this sometimes without it being mixed with a tastier food, but my two older cats don't like it at all and the two old ferals outside don't love it either. I mix it with the wet food they love and they eat most of it, but I probably won't buy it again...at least this flavor.
customer_reviews.author: Marcy Powell

customer_reviews.title: My cats refuse to eat this!
customer_reviews.text: I have an overweight, typically ravenous cat. We were switching to grain-free diet in the hope of helping him shed some pounds. Our other cat will eat anything from a can. Except this. I don't know if it's spoiled, but we are very disappointed, and the case we purchased is simply a waste. I will add that they did eat the dry kibble in this brand, so their reaction to this is puzzling. Reviews indicated this would be a good purchase.
customer_reviews.author: Ryn1010

customer_reviews.title: Disgusting
customer_reviews.text: Opened this box with ants crawling all over, smelled like something died in it....i almost threw up it was so disgusting and everything in it had maggots and antbabies crawling in it
customer_reviews.author: Therapist

customer_reviews.title: One Star
customer_reviews.text: Food was a really odd texture. Kitty wouldn't finish it and he will literally eat anything in sight. 👎🏻
customer_reviews.author: Liz hicks

customer_reviews.title: Quality not the same
customer_reviews.text: I purchased this online to save the time of having to go to the store. The cans arrived on time and were packaged well. However, every can I've opened so far are not of the same quality that I've purchased from the store. My cats are eating it but it just doesn't look right. The color and consistency are off. I'm not sure if this was substituted or not...the label and everything is the same as the store bought but there's a definite difference in the product in the can.
customer_reviews.author: V.Bell

customer_reviews.title: Great for a Special-Needs Cat
customer_reviews.text: I have what could politely be described as a "special-needs cat." She's moody, older, is missing many of her teeth, and has some serious dietary concerns. So many foods cause her to wretch or otherwise have discomfort. I've found I can give her a can of this in the evening and keep this version of the dry food out for her all day as a snack, and she doesn't get sick. If not for the price, I'd give this to her twice a day. As it is, though, using this in the evening and the dry all day is working fine. This is also the flavor she likes the best.
customer_reviews.author: Rachel K

customer_reviews.title: More like soup than canned meat
customer_reviews.text: Too much water - makes it an expensive soup-like mixture - and causes the kittens to get it all over the surrounding floor and walk in it, because it literally drips out of their mouths. Using paper plates which is what many people do to avoid having to wash cat dishes - it soaks into the paper immediately - and you are forced to use 3 or 4 paper plates to contain this soupy mixture for more than a few seconds.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Bad batch???
customer_reviews.text: My cat would not eat any of the food from this shipment. I bought the exact same food locally and put them side by side in his bowl. He ate the locally bought food, but not any of the one bought on Amazon. I checked the expiration date and it was still good. I am not sure what the issue was.
customer_reviews.author: Pamela

customer_reviews.title: My cat seems to think its great
customer_reviews.text: Not sure what these other people are talking about. This cat food smells the same as the kind I buy at Petco. My cat likes it just fine. Even though the smell is a bit offensive it's not as offensive as the other wet cheaper cat food and their poop doesn't smell nearly as bad as when they eat the cheap stuff.
customer_reviews.author: Chris

customer_reviews.title: Why is there ground up bones in this cat food?
customer_reviews.text: My cat won't eat this food. So disappointed with Blue Buffalo. Is this company lying about the ingredients in their cat food? There are lots of what appears to be ground up bone pieces in this food. I've picked out some of the white pieces and tried to crush them. They don't crush and are hard like bone. There have been and there continues to be many law suits against blue buffalo for false advertising /ingredients. I suggest anyone considering buying blue buffalo cat and/or dog food to google "law suits against blue buffalo". I won't be buying any Blue Buffalo or Wilderness cat food anymore.
customer_reviews.author: Diann D.

customer_reviews.title: Not for my cat!
customer_reviews.text: Opened up the can to find contents runny and very grey. Cat refused to go near it. Too late to return as it was part of a three carton order two chicken, which were fine, and the salmon. Very disappointed as this is $30 down the drain. Lesson to only order one carton at a time.
customer_reviews.author: PHirsc

customer_reviews.title: Olivia likes it
customer_reviews.text: Olivia, the cat residing with us, has demonstrated great appreciation for the varieties of Blue Buffalo Wilderness. This morning she ate a half can of chicken and then fell into a food induced coma. Doubtless she will want something other than chicken at the next meal, but it again will render her sated and sleepy. I have noticed her playing more upon awakening, so the food may also give her more energy (she is 18). I can say with conviction that she will want me to order more as the current supply dwindles.
customer_reviews.author: Kindle Customer

customer_reviews.title: Good value but it's true, the consistency can be off.
customer_reviews.text: After making several purchases of Blue Buffalo Wilderness wet cat food, the consistency can be off on each package. Some cans spill out completely wet and mushy. While other cans can be perfect. I'm not sure what weather conditions these are supposed to be stored in, but it may be a storage issue. They are a healthier option for my cat than fancy feast, so I'll continue to purchase them until the quality gets worse.
customer_reviews.author: EST. LEE DISPLAY L D 1902

customer_reviews.title: My cats don’t like it

I didn’t realize that this was pate style when I ordered it. My cats don’t really like pate anyway but there’s something about this flavor that is particularly off-putting to them.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Cats aren't impressed

Right away I noticed it was mushier than the previous wet food I'd been using. Only one cat would eat it, and even then he only nibbled at it. I'm going to try mixing it with the other food I have to see if that helps otherwise it's getting donated. I keep forgetting the cardinal rule with cats. Always buy a single can first to see if they like it before buying a case.
customer_reviews.author: Iamthecatalyst

customer_reviews.title: Kitty loves it!
customer_reviews.text: I was previously feeding my cat Fancy Feast before I realized how many bad ingredients it has. Unfortunately, she loved the stuff and I was having a hard time finding something she loved as much--until this! She LOVES this food and eats it up so quickly. My cat is not a picky eater but this has been the only one I've found that she eats in one sitting. The price is great and is about $10 cheaper than anywhere else I've seen. Very happy with this!

customer_reviews.title: So nasty

customer_reviews.author: Varie

customer_reviews.title: It's the only wet food my geriatric cat loves.
customer_reviews.text: I haven't tried it and I'm not planning on doing so (unless the world goes seriously, seriously wrong) so I can't comment on whether this tastes better than other brands. I can however say that my 16+ y\o cat with bad teeth loves it, and he's been a notoriously picky eater. in a pinch, we can get by with other Blue Buffalo wet food, as long as it's pate, and its poultry, but the duck is still his favorite. My only complaint is that they don't make the duck in a bigger can as they do with the chicken.

I can't find a case of only the Salmon pate anywhere else and am very disappointed I purchased this!

customer_reviews.title: Cat loves it.

He wakes me up hollering at me to feed him. He never did that before until I started him on this stuff. My other two don't seem to touch it; but I'm only assuming. I've actually never seen my fattest cat (20lbs) eat anything. He doesn't like any kind of treats. My as*hole cat, (11lbs), loves the treats from tubes but walks away from this canned stuff. FYI: I keep dried food (also from Blue Wilderness) in a gravity feeder for all day snacking.
customer_reviews.author: goldngemgirl

customer_reviews.title: My Senior Loves It!

The turkey alone was on sale for $21 for a case of 24 5.5oz cans and after I read the reviews, I decided to go ahead and try it. I'm REALLY glad I did! She absolutely loves the taste and it's healthy. I personally love the fact that the pate is softer than most pates in its consistency, while still holding its shape.
customer_reviews.author: SciFiFan

customer_reviews.title: Picky cat loves it

Since she was mostly outdoors all her 14+ years, she's been a bit picky about what she eats. Since she also has lost many teeth and has a tendency for UTIs, I wanted simple, grain-free, real (and wet) food for her. I'm using a mixture of this, the Chicken formula and the low-ingredient Turkey formula. She's been eating it right up and we're on our 4th case now, so I think this is going to do it for us.
customer_reviews.author: 🌈 KT

customer_reviews.author: Diane M Murphy

customer_reviews.text: Using this brand for my KC old kitty. This has fewest fillers and still somewhat affordable compared to truly "raw" / minimal ingredient wet cat foods. Keeps kitty interested in eating. Phosphate binder added makes it better for my kitty with bad kidneys.

customer_reviews.author: CMOK

customer_reviews.title: Cat's aren't dumb, neither are dogs
customer_reviews.text: Had to change cat food due to cat having allergies... tried every blue buffalo product they offer including dry food, cats won't touch it or even look at it. Tried to feed it to dogs they wouldn't eat it.. animals aren't dumb. Expensive and texture is strange.
customer_reviews.author: BLUESKYS4ME

customer_reviews.title: Wilderness chicken pate
customer_reviews.text: At first the animal wouldn't eat it altho he liked Wilderness in other flavors like rabbit and bison. However, he has now gotten to love it. Looking forward to finding other flavors. The vet said that some cats have trouble with the richness of the Wilderness meat. Not ours. He was having problems with Friskies and that's why we switched.
customer_reviews.author: catsnout

customer_reviews.title: They won't eat it - and they eat anything
customer_reviews.text: My shelter rescues hardly ever got wet food, but they will not eat this. I ended up donating it to a vet's holiday food drive. Hopefully, some other cat enjoyed it. The company was great and refunded my money, but I'd rather have a food my cats like.
customer_reviews.author: awgoodkitty

customer_reviews.title: Soup???
customer_reviews.text: Miss Kitty loves it... However, it is quite soupy... Not a fan of how liquidy it is. Curious as to whether or not it is supposed to be that way... Did I just pay for water downed food?
customer_reviews.author: Kasandra Barber

customer_reviews.title: Inconsistent batches. Smells good one batch, foul the next.
customer_reviews.text: Bought the Chicken flavored wet cat food two months in a row. Cat loved it, and I thought I was weird because even I thought it smelled kinda tasty. Third month, suddenly its like a completely different food. It smells absolutely foul, and my cat won't even touch it. Honestly don't blame him. It smells almost as bad as the Salmon flavored wet cat food of the same brand that his previous owners gave me when I adopted him. You'd think this would be an easy thing to keep consistent but I guess not.
customer_reviews.author: Colin Swan

customer_reviews.title: Best food
customer_reviews.text: Best brand of food. used to buy cheap food, only saved like 5 bucks doing that. G/f talked me into blue buffalo cause her dog eats it. My cats have never been sick and are ultra healthy, the male is really muscular. Will never cheapen out on cat food again. Saving on vet bills
customer_reviews.author: Ryan Kallenberg

customer_reviews.title: Our cat loves this food!
customer_reviews.text: I bought this to supplement our cat's dry food meals. He didn't care for the fish and salmon flavors, but he seems to enjoy the chicken. He was losing some weight in his older age (14 yo)...supplementing with this food has helped him maintain his weight.
customer_reviews.author: TJoi

customer_reviews.title: We are happy and so are our furry overlords
customer_reviews.text: We wanted to move exclusively to wet food feeding from dry and wet, because our felines were becoming quite hefty. This brand seemed to hit a good balance between being on the healthier side, while not costing an arm and a leg. The picky little brats actually like it, there’s far less regurgitation than with hard food, and they’ve lost some pounds! They can actually jump over things now! All parties are pleased.
customer_reviews.author: J. Stronk

customer_reviews.title: Damaged cans
customer_reviews.text: I like most of this company’s cat food products and my cat Yoyo does Too. But with the last case, Moses of the cans were severely dented. This must have happened before the case was packaged because the damaged cans were throughout the case.
customer_reviews.author: Lynn Circe

customer_reviews.title: I guess they're like me who hates what's good for me and loves ...
customer_reviews.text: I've had nothing but failure trying to get my cats to eat healthy food. After many other canned cat foods, my three felines ate this and a few other flavors. However, after about 3 weeks they just stopped eating it. Sigh! I guess they're like me who hates what's good for me and loves food with sugar and all the other addictive junk that passes as "food" in the supermarket.
customer_reviews.author: Susan

customer_reviews.title: cat food
customer_reviews.text: no good my cats do not want to eat it and too watery.
customer_reviews.author: Monique K.

customer_reviews.title: Good cat food. Poor packaging.
customer_reviews.text: Kitty loves it! It was her first non-kitten food now she’s old enough. My only concern is that they need to be more careful with their packaging since one of the tins was cracked, open and leaking over the others.
customer_reviews.author: hcl

customer_reviews.title: My not picky cat hates this
customer_reviews.text: My cat has never been a picky eater. She doesn't like the salmon flavor. She even will beg for kibble when she gets this one. Won't be buying this again.
customer_reviews.author: Sophia Nukuto

customer_reviews.title: Great flavor that my cats love!
customer_reviews.text: I have been buying this for years now and my cats always finish this first over other flavors they may get. The quality seems to be great and it keeps them happy! Thanks!!!
customer_reviews.author: Capixaba

customer_reviews.title: Disappointed :-(
customer_reviews.text: The ad says 24 cans but received 2 cans. Our cat did not like this food ended up throwing it away. Next time you purchase something like this, make sure you read the complete description and details.
customer_reviews.author: SoozyQ

customer_reviews.title: Not the same quality as if purchased locally
customer_reviews.text: I don't know why this was different than what can be purchased locally, but all three of my cats won't touch it. It looks and smells rancid and has a soupy texture. Something is wrong with the last few batches I received. I cancelled my subscription and will buy from the big chain locally instead.
customer_reviews.author: Bonnie J.

customer_reviews.title: Magic cat food.
customer_reviews.text: My cats love this so much it makes me feel like they think they're kibble is garbage food. I let my husband feed them this canned food as a kind of bribe, and they like him noticeably more now...
customer_reviews.author: lmp51557

customer_reviews.title: Best thing you can do for your cat
customer_reviews.text: It seems like they fixed their quality control issues because I didn’t see any problems with the batch I received. On to the praise: I had been feeding my cat Trader Joe’s wet food and I noticed it was making his fur dull, giving him chin acne, and making him generally lethargic. About three days after feeding this to him he was like a different cat. His fur became sleek and soft, he lost weight and became more muscular and limber, and his personality changed. He was much more alert and engaging. It sounds like an exaggeration but it’s not. It’s a great food for a great price.
customer_reviews.author: Rose Guthrie

customer_reviews.title: Keeps cats hydrated, fed, and healthy
customer_reviews.text: One of my cats was vomiting hairballs at least once a week (sometimes a few times a week) when we had her on dry food made by blue wilderness. She also has an allergy to poultry food (chicken and duck both cause her problems). Our other cat was not getting enough water from dry foods and was developing UTIs. Switching to this wet food (half a can for each cat once a day) has solved the allergies, dehydration, and hairball vomiting. It has been one month now without any of the described problems occurring.
customer_reviews.author: Corvin Barnette

customer_reviews.title: Good price/Very watery
customer_reviews.text: Update: The first time I ordered this it was great. The second time I ordered it. It was very watery. My cat is not as fond of this batch Great pricing. My cat likes it and that’s all I need to know.
customer_reviews.author: Clm

customer_reviews.title: Optimum Nutrition
customer_reviews.text: We have a bengal rescue and after researching the ingredients this product gives our cat the best combination of daily requirements needed for optimum health. He’s very picky about the flavors he likes but they’re always available. Great product.
customer_reviews.author: Dennis Ward

customer_reviews.title: Good Food
customer_reviews.text: Just opening the can you can tell this is good food - it actually smells like ground up turkey instead of that typical 'catfood' smell. It keeps well with a plastic catfood lid in the fridge, though the moisture does tend to come out as it gets that 'jelly' that cooked meat does when cold. It's packed very densely and takes some smushing to mix well with water after being chilled, and the 'jelly' never quite mixes into the water, but my my cat loves it.
customer_reviews.author: FantasyFan

customer_reviews.title: Worse than most wet cat foods
customer_reviews.text: While most wet cat food we have purchased looks like a somewhat appealing version of pate, this wet cat food looked awful. The cans have at least 3 or 4 times more oil than other wet foods, and the pate itself looks like another cat already chewed it up and spit it back out. I definitely don’t recommend this wet food.
customer_reviews.author: Hunter

customer_reviews.title: My cats do not like it
customer_reviews.text: I have been buying Blue buff in 5.5 oz cans for quite a time. Never had an issue. Tried this pack of 12 oz and what a waste! My all 3 cats do not like it! Something is wrong!
customer_reviews.author: Marina

customer_reviews.title: Cheaper option for the single protein counterpart
customer_reviews.text: I got this as a cheaper option to the Blue Buffalo Duck and Potato single protein food. My cat is allergic to chicken and fish, and this agitated her stomach a little bit. I will probably stick to the single protein brand of this to avoid future messes, but it is a great lower cost option if your cat has a stronger stomach than mine (which is easy to do)! My other cat who has no allergies loved this.
customer_reviews.author: Elizabeth

customer_reviews.title: Not good texture.
customer_reviews.text: While I’ve had great success with the dry Blue Buffalo products I can’t say the same about its wet food. Essentially it’s too wet. To me that means it’s a filler to increase the weight of the product. More water, less solid food. I won’t be buying this again.
customer_reviews.author: Figaro Kaiju

customer_reviews.title: As expected and cats love it too
customer_reviews.text: Wet food is fine and as expected. It does smell extra fishy though, as far as wet food goes. It was a great price for good quality wet food. No dented cans or quality concerns for me.
customer_reviews.author: Lisa Angel

customer_reviews.title: Too complex of flavors.
customer_reviews.text: I'm sure that there is nothing wrong with the flavor of this for many cats, but my cat really won't touch this flavor. I call this Turducken. Maybe this is too complex of a mixture for her
customer_reviews.author: Michael D. Steinacher

customer_reviews.title: Great for Older Cata
customer_reviews.text: Purchased for my 17 yo cat. I wanted her to have a good quality food at a reasonable price, and this is the wet food for her. She eats it well and doesn’t let it linger in her bowl all day.
customer_reviews.author: Tilda

customer_reviews.title: No Bueno
customer_reviews.text: My cat will not even touch this, he started to eat the duck, but after 2 bites walked away. The salmon is like vomit, all liquid, doesn't seem appealing even for cat food. But this is the 2nd time I bought this, thinking the 1st one was spoiled or something and this one looks identical. Opague and loose. Waste of 40 dollars.
customer_reviews.author: Greggory L Burrows

customer_reviews.title: Judging flavor based on my cat's preference -- not personal experience ;-)
customer_reviews.text: I have a senior cat, a finicky eater. This is the one brand and the one flavor she will eat consistently. Sometimes I feed her the "kitten" version, which has a lower water content and is a thicker consistency
customer_reviews.author: Elyse V Gura

customer_reviews.title: Delicious
customer_reviews.text: I know this blue buffalo canned cat food is delicious because not only do my cats eat it but my wife and I eat it as well. Our favorite is grilled cheese canned blue Buffalo cat food on rye.
customer_reviews.author: David Theis

customer_reviews.title: Convenient
customer_reviews.text: My cat is allergic to chicken and beef, finding food she likes is really hard, she loves this stuff and Amazon has the best price, definitely a win-win for me!
customer_reviews.author: Whitney

customer_reviews.title: Kitty's Fav
customer_reviews.text: I have an older cat & she's real picky. She needed soft food, so this was the best on the market. Best thing is that her litter box doesn't smell because of the quality of the food.
customer_reviews.author: Rodneys Girl

product_meta.title: Blue Buffalo Wilderness High Protein Grain Free, Natural Adult Pate Wet Cat Food
product_meta.description: Flavor Name:Duck Pate Recipe| Size:3 oz (Pack of 24)Inspired by the diet of the lynx, Blue Wilderness duck recipe is a high-protein food that will provide your cat with a higher concentration of the Duck she loves. Blue wilderness natural cat food is also a sensible alternative to less convenient raw diets, which often require additional supplementation to be nutritionally complete.
feature_bullets: PACKED WITH REAL DUCK: This grain free cat food contains more of the duck cats love to provide the energy your adult cat needs to stay active
PATÉ STYLE CANNED CAT FOOD: This high protein cat food features a smooth texture your feline friend can’t resist
NATURAL CAT FOOD: All BLUE canned cat foods are made with the finest natural ingredients enhanced with vitamins and minerals

MADE WITHOUT WHEAT: BLUE wet cat food contains NO chicken (or poultry) by-product meals, NO corn, wheat (a common thickening agent used by many other brands) or soy, and NO artificial flavors or preservatives
Contains twenty four (24) 3-oz cans of BLUE Wilderness High Protein Grain Free, Natural Adult Pate Wet Cat Food, Duck
